Package: xfce4-power-manager
Section: xfce
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, hal, 
 xfce4-power-manager-data (=${source:Version})
Suggests: xfce4-power-manager-plugins
Description: power manager for Xfce desktop
 Power manager for the Xfce desktop, laptop users can set up a power profile
 for two different modes "on battery power" and "on ac power", desktop users
 still can change DPMS settings and CPU frequency using the settings dialog.
 .
 It features:
   * battery monitoring
   * cpu frequency settings
   * monitor DPMS settings
   * suspend/Hibernate
   * LCD brightness control
   * Lid, sleep and power switches control

Package: xfce4-power-manager-data
Section: xfce
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: xfce4-power-manager
Replaces: xfce4-power-manager (< 0.8.0~beta2-1)
Description: power manager for Xfce desktop, arch-indep files
 Power manager for the Xfce desktop, laptop users can set up a power profile
 for two different modes "on battery power" and "on ac power", desktop users
 still can change DPMS settings and CPU frequency using the settings dialog.
 .
 This package contains architecture-independant files.

Package: xfce4-power-manager-plugins
Section: xfce
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, 
 xfce4-power-manager (>= 0.8.0~)
Description: power manager plugins for Xfce panel
 Power manager for the Xfce desktop, laptop users can set up a power profile
 for two different modes "on battery power" and "on ac power", desktop users
 still can change DPMS settings and CPU frequency using the settings dialog.
 .
 This package contains two panel plugins, inhibit and brightness.
